# Generation feature flags (Perf Flags)

When shipping a **new player-visible or perf-bisectable plaza system**, register a toggle in the same change. Do not leave ungated systems that Features / Dev QA cannot isolate.

## Canonical files

| Piece                         | File                                                                                          |
| ----------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Ids, groups, labels, defaults | `definingWorldPlazaGenerationFeatureRegistry.ts`                                              |
| Runtime gate                  | `checkingWorldPlazaGenerationFeatureEnabled` in `managingWorldPlazaGenerationFeatureStore.ts` |
| Badge priority (optional)     | `definingWorldPlazaPerformanceDiagnosticsFlagBadgeConstants.ts`                               |
| Blank slate                   | Dev QA builds from registry; new ids default **off** there                                    |

## Checklist (every new flag)

1. Add `SCREAMING_SNAKE` key + kebab-case string id to `DEFINING_WORLD_PLAZA_GENERATION_FEATURE`.
2. Add registry row: `featureId`, `groupId`, short `label`, one-line `description` (what Off does).
3. Add default `true` in `DEFINING_WORLD_PLAZA_GENERATION_FEATURE_DEFAULTS`.
4. Gate hot path with `checkingWorldPlazaGenerationFeatureEnabled(...)`.
5. If wildlife presentation nuance (no terrain cache), add id to the early-return list in `invalidatingWorldPlazaGenerationFeatureCachesDeferred`.
6. Optionally prepend id in `DEFINING_WORLD_PLAZA_PERFORMANCE_DIAGNOSTICS_FLAG_PRIORITY_ORDER`.

## Group picker (`groupId`)

| Group      | Use for                                            |
| ---------- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| `world`    | Biome / elevation / shape of the map               |
| `terrain`  | Trees, rocks, floor bake, stone decor              |
| `water`    | Ocean, lakes, rivers, streams, ponds               |
| `hazards`  | Lava and similar damage fields                     |
| `entities` | Wildlife spawn/sim/render and wildlife sub-toggles |
| `hud`      | DOM overlays, minimap, bars, status chrome         |
| `systems`  | Audio, projectiles, lighting, fire, combat FX      |

Prefer a **child flag** under an existing parent when Off only strips a slice (e.g. wildlife speech under `entities`, not a new group).

## When to add a flag

**Yes:** new terrain layer, entity system, HUD chrome, audio bus, lighting/fire, hazard, wildlife presentation cost, anything Dev QA blank slate should kill.

**No:** pure helpers, tests, renames, tiny constants, copy-only edits, internals already fully covered by a parent flag.

## Gate patterns

```typescript
// ✅ Early-return / skip work
if (!checkingWorldPlazaGenerationFeatureEnabled(
  DEFINING_WORLD_PLAZA_GENERATION_FEATURE.MY_FEATURE
)) {
  return;
}

// ✅ Terrain layer descriptor
requiresAnyGenerationFeature: [
  DEFINING_WORLD_PLAZA_GENERATION_FEATURE.MY_FEATURE,
],
```

```typescript
// ❌ Hardcoded true/false or a second ad-hoc localStorage key
```

## Naming

- Id string: kebab-case (`wildlife-fairy-glow`)
- Const key: matching SCREAMING_SNAKE
- Label: short UI title; description: player/dev-facing Off behavior
